ite rules. The tool was used for building the <a href=\"http://oldhungariancorpus.nytud.hu/\">Old Hungarian Corpus</a>.", "Functionality": ["normalization"], "Domain": "historical texts", "Language": ["Hungarian"], "Licence": "", "Platform": [], "Infrastructure": "HUN-CLARIN", "Input format": ["unspecified"], "Output format": ["unspecified"], "Access": {}, "Publication": "https://www.zotero.org/groups/562080/clarin/collections/UZKYZV3N/items/YX6JCMDC/"}, {"Name": "PICCL: Philosophical Integrator of Computational and Corpus Libraries", "URL": "https://portal.clarin.ivdnt.org/piccl/", "Family": "Tools for Normalisation", "Description": "This is a set of workflows for corpus building through OCR, post-correction, modernization of historic language and Natural Language Processing. It combines <a href=\"https://opensource.google/projects/tesseract\">Tesseract Optical Character Recognition</a>, <a href=\"https://portal.clarin.nl/node/14376\">TICCL</a> and <a href=\"https://languagemachines.github.io/frog\">FROG</a> functionality in a single pipeline.", "Functionality": ["OCR", "normalization", "tokenisation", "dependency parsing", "shallow parsing", "lemmatization", "morphological analysis", "NER", "PoS-tagging"], "Domain": "independent", "Language": ["Dutch", "Swedish", "Russian", "Spanish", "Portuguese", "English", "German", "French", "Italian", "Finnish", "Greek", "Ancient Greek", "Icelandic", "German (Fraktur)", "Latin", "Romanian"], "Licence": "GNU GPL", "Platform": ["cross-platform"], "Infrastructure": "CLARIAH-NL", "Input format": ["images (tiff, vnd.djvu)", "plain text", "xml"], "Output format": ["FoLiA XML"], "Access": {"Download": "https://github.com/LanguageMachines/piccl"}, "Publication": "https://www.zotero.org/groups/562080/clarin/collections/UZKYZV3N/items/TLAPMXY2/"}, {"Name": "Korektor", "URL": "http://lindat.cz/services/korektor/", "Family": "Tools for Normalisation", "Description": "Korektor is a statistical spellchecker and (occasional) grammar checker released under <a href=\"http://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-2-Clause\">2-Clause BSD license</a> and versioned using <a href=\"http://semver.org/\">Semantic Versioning</a>.\nKorektor started with Michal Richter's diploma thesis <a href=\"https://redmine.ms.mff.cuni.cz/documents/1\">Advanced Czech Spellchecker</a>, but it is being developed further. There are two versions: a command line utility (tested on Linux, Windows and OS X) and a REST service with <a href=\"https://lindat.mff.cuni.cz/services/korektor/api-reference.php\">publicly available API</a> and <a href=\"https://lindat.mff.cuni.cz/services/korektor/\">HTML front end</a>.", "Functionality": ["normalization"], "Domain": "", "Language": ["Czech"], "Licence": "CC-BY-NC-A (models)", "Platform": ["Linux", "OS X", "Windows"], "Infrastructure": "LINDAT", "Input format": ["plain text"], "Output format": ["enriched text"], "Access": {"Web service": "https://lindat.mff.cuni.cz/services/korektor/", "API": "https://lindat.mff.cuni.cz/services/korektor/api-reference.php"}, "Publication": "Rhttps://www.zotero.org/groups/562080/clarin/collections/UZKYZV3N/items/X9ESN2EQ/"}, {"Name": "CSMTiser", "URL": "https://github.com/clarinsi/csmtiser", "Family": "Tools for Normalisation", "Description": "This is a trainable tool for text normalisation, based on <a href=\"http://www.statmt.org/moses/\">Moses</a>.", "Functionality": ["normalization"], "Domain": "social media", "Language": ["Slovenian"], "Licence": "GNU Lesser General Public License v3.0", "Platform": ["Linux"], "Infrastructure": "CLARIN.SI", "Input format": ["unspecified"], "Output format": ["unspecified"], "Access": {"Download": "https://github.com/clarinsi/csmtiser"}, "Publication": "https://www.zotero.org/groups/562080/clarin/collections/UZKYZV3N/items/89P3ZT7L/"}, {"Name": "CAB orthographic canonicalizer", "URL": "http://hdl.handle.net/11858/00-203C-0000-0023-21BB-3", "Family": "Tools for Normalisation", "Description": "This tool a WebLicht stub for the <a href=\"http://odo.dwds.de/~jurish/software/DTA-CAB/\">DTA::CAB</a> service and provides orthographic normalization for historical German.", "Functionality": ["normalisation"], "Domain": "historical texts", "Language": ["German"], "Licence": "", "Platform": ["cross-platform"], "Infrastructure": "CLARIN-D", "Input format": ["plain text", "XML"], "Output format": ["unspecified"], "Access": {"Web application": "https://www.deutschestextarchiv.de/public/cab/?fmt=tcf-orth"}, "Publication": ""}, {"Name": "CAB historical text analysis", "URL": "http://hdl.handle.net/21.11120/0000-0003-7D99-5", "Family": "Tools for Normalisation", "Description": "This tool is a WebLicht stub for the <a href=\"http://odo.dwds.de/~jurish/software/DTA-CAB/\">DTA::CAB</a> service and provides orthographic normalisation, PoS-tagging and lemmatization for historical German.", "Functionality": ["normalisation", "PoS-tagging", "lemmatisation"], "Domain": "historical texts", "Language": ["German"], "Licence": "", "Platform": ["cross-platform"], "Infrastructure": "CLARIN-D", "Input format": ["plain text", "XML"], "Output format": ["<a href=\"https://universaldependencies.org/tagset-conversion/de-stts-uposf.html\">stts</a> tagset for PoS"], "Access": {"Web application": "https://www.deutschestextarchiv.de/public/cab/?fmt=tcf"}, "Publication": ""}, {"Name": "Nederlab Pipeline", "URL": "https://github.com/proycon/nederlab-pipeline", "Family": "Tools for Normalisation", "Description": "This is a linguistic enrichment pipeline for Historical Dutch as developed for and used in the <a href=\"https://www.nederlab.nl/\">Nederlab project</a>. This workflow, powered by <a href=\"https://www.nextflow.io/\">Nextflow</a>, invokes various tools, including <a href=\"https://languagemachines.github.io/frog\">Frog</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/LanguageMachines/piccl\">FoLiA-wordtranslate</a>, as well as other tools such as <a href=\"https://languagemachines.github.io/ucto\">ucto</a> (a tokeniser), <a href=\"https://github.com/proycon/foliatools\">folialangid</a> (language identification), <a href=\"https://github.com/proycon/foliatools\">tei2folia</a> (conversion from a subset of TEI to FoLiA, which serves as the exchange format for all our tooling, as well as the final corpus format for Nederlab). Due to the high complexity in tooling, this workflow and all dependencies are distributed as part of the <a href=\"https://proycon.github.io/LaMachine\">LaMachine</a> distribution.", "Functionality": ["modernisation, normalisation, tokenisation, conversion, PoS-tagging, lemmatisation, NER with entity linking (all functionality is derived from the individual parts rather than an inherent part of the workflow)"], "Domain": "independent", "Language": ["Dutch"], "Licence": "GNU Public License v3", "Platform": ["Linux/POSIX (workflow itself runs on JVM, underlying components are mostly implemented in C++ and Python)"], "Infrastructure": "CLARIAH-NL", "Input format": ["FoLiA XML"], "Output format": ["FoLiA XML"], "Access": {"Download": "https://github.com/proycon/nederlab-pipeline/"}, "Publication": "https://www.zotero.org/groups/562080/clarin/collections/UZKYZV3N/items/MXWFHFAS/"}]